ID=gene-AT1G50240;Dbxref=Araport:AT1G50240,TAIR:AT1G50240,GeneID:841446;Name=FU;Note=The FUSED (FU) gene belongs to Ser/Thr protein kinase family and has a key role in the hedgehog signaling pathway known to control cell proliferation and patterning in fruit flies and humans . Arabidopsis thaliana genome has a single Fu gene. Cytokinesis-defective mutants%2C which we named two-in-one (tio)%2C result from mutations in Arabidopsis Fu. Phenotypic analysis of tio mutants reveals an essential role for TIO in conventional modes of cytokinesis in plant meristems and during male gametogenesis.
